{
  "stem": "7093.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And we used to go into the mountains nearly every Sunday, or very, very often.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We went into the mountains and went over the border regularly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "So the border guards knew us quite well.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And so all my grandmother and-- and my aunt all sent down jewels and all kinds of belongings to patients in-- on the Australian side.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And we went over every Sunday and brought over.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "So we were sitting in the-- in the forest on a Persian carpet, eating with silver-- [LAUGHTER] in silver dishes, which was rather funny.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "When the-- I mean, so that we were using those for the border guards who let us through, who-- And we brought over everything, I mean, lots of things, incredible amount of things from--",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was-- there was no difficulty at all for us to bring it over.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, of course, everything was lost anyway later on. in 19-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] so when I was 15-- this was in '38.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In-- when I was the 15, my Austrian family, who in the meantime emigrated, they kept on writing-- except my grandmother and quite a few of my mother's cousins who didn't manage to get out and who were then deported and never heard of again.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My, those who got out, they all wrote, make her learn a trade.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Take her out of school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's much better if she knows to do something with their hands.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So at the age of 15, I was taken out of school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was put into a milliners-- as a milliner's apprentice, which I did for the next two years.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I hated every minute of it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In the evening, after every day after school-- after work, my father took me for an hour.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had tuition from him.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
